The paper discusses the process of knowledge mobilization and translation, specifically in the context of academia and industry collaborations. This involves the sharing of ideas and showcasing of results, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of technology and the analysis of data also suggest a possible connection to social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the focus on collaborative work and the sharing of ideas suggests a possible connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
